EAST LONDON - South Africa beat Bangladesh by 200 runs in the third one-day international at Buffalo Park on Sunday. Faf Du Plessis top scored with 91 for the South Africans before retiring hurt as they posted 369 for six, their highest one-day total against Bangladesh and the highest total at the ground. Bangladesh were then bowled out for 169 in reply despite 63 from Shakib Al Hasan as South Africa secured a 3-0 victory in the three-match series. AFP